  - Jarocinski-Karadi
  - Altavilla-EA-MPD
abstract: |
  Companion code repository for a Bachelor (BSc) thesis on high-frequency
  identification of equity-bond comovement. Pre-registered pipeline with
  7 modular packages, 462 unit tests, two-stage gate methodology, and
  bootstrap inference. Findings: (i) NFP/neg structural channel identified
  robust to multiple bond-piece specifications; (ii) ECB QE factor
  transmission monotonic along Bund 3M-30Y curve with significance at 30Y;
  (iii) residual third channel (L, V, C) not identified under pre-registered
  q=0.10; (iv) identification does not imply out-of-sample predictability:
  the event-driven strategy built on identified findings does not survive
  out-of-sample without ex-post filter selection on small samples,
  reported as honest negative result.
